@Matt

Actually, assuming no air resistance, the path is actually an arc of an ellipse rather than that of a parabola. It's a parabola if one assumes that the acceleration of gravity is constant. That assumption is very nearly correct when the tossed object traverses a short arc.

However, since the acceleration of gravity is not a constant, the equations of motion yield an elliptical arc. Of course, a parabolic approximation is completely suitable in this case, but the arc is, technically, that of an ellipse.

